INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436001, 'Just be patient. Let the game come to you. Don''t rush. Be quick, but don''t hurry.', 69643, 0), (436002, 'The best kids are going to become the best. But the best thing about it is that you''re going to learn lessons in playing those sports about winning and losing and teamwork and teammates and arguments and everything else that are going to affect you positively for the rest of your life.', 38471, 0), (436003, 'Sports is the common denominator in the world that brings everyone together. If there''s any one place in the world where there is equality, it is probably sports. That was something that didn''t always exist. We''ve come a long way in sports. Why can''t society use sports as a way to bring people together and create change?', 69644, 0), (436004, 'At school I pretended I had a normal life, but I felt lonely all the time and different from everyone else. I never felt like I fit in, and I wasn''t allowed to participate in after-school activities, go to sports events or parties or date boys. Many times I had to make up stories about why I couldn''t do anything with my classmates.', 1206, 0), (436005, 'I am in the fighting game. I don''t care about anything else. I don''t watch the news, I don''t care about politics, I don''t care about other sports. I don''t care about anything I don''t need to care about. This is my sport: it is my life. I study it; I think about it all the time. Nothing else matters.', 56476, 0), (436006, 'To find a man''s true character, play golf with him.', 273, 0), (436007, 'One man practicing sportsmanship is far better than a hundred teaching it.', 59446, 0), (436008, 'The world of sports knows no religious, racial or political differences. Athletes, from whatever land they come, speak the same language. The lessons of competition are lessons for life.', 60667, 0), (436009, 'Fishing is much more than fish. It is the great occasion when we may return to the fine simplicity of our forefathers.', 7777, 0), (436010, 'Show me a good loser, and I''ll show you a loser.', 5571, 0), (436011, 'People ask me what I do in winter when there''s no baseball. I''ll tell you what I do. I stare out the window and wait for spring.', 69645, 0), (436012, 'I think what endurance sports teach you is to stay dedicated, stay focused, and also to understand you''re going to have ups and downs, but you need to keep running right through them.', 69646, 0), (436013, 'We didn''t lose the game we just ran out of time. ', 5571, 0), (436014, 'You don''t play against opponents, you play against the game of basketball.', 7610, 0), (436015, 'You wouldn''t have won if we''d beaten you.', 1896, 0), (436016, 'It''s good sportsmanship to not pick up lost golf balls while they are still rolling.', 286, 0), (436017, 'Skiing combines outdoor fun with knocking down trees with your face.', 2223, 0), (436018, 'My motto was always to keep swinging. Whether I was in a slump or feeling badly or having trouble off the field, the only thing to do was keep swinging.', 59444, 0), (436019, 'Sports is a metaphor for overcoming obstacles and achieving against great odds. Athletes, in times of difficulty, can be important role models.', 65802, 0), (436020, 'I see great things in baseball. It''s our game - the American game.', 1127, 0), (436021, 'Thanks to the competence, love of God, our country''s security and stability, endowed wealth, integrated infrastructure and quality services, the U.A.E. turned into the world''s renowned destination for tourism, investment and business management: the interface of choice for hosting major cultural events, artistic and sports, in the world.', 69647, 0), (436022, 'To me, it doesn''t matter how good you are. Sport is all about playing and competing. Whatever you do in cricket and in sport, enjoy it, be positive and try to win.', 69648, 0), (436023, 'The two most important things in life are good friends and a strong bullpen.', 63857, 0), (436024, 'There are only two seasons - winter and Baseball.', 59461, 0), (436025, 'Baseball is the only field of endeavor where a man can succeed three times out of ten and be considered a good performer.', 9815, 0), (436026, 'All of the sports have a safety net, but boxing is the only sport that has none. So when the fighter is through, he is through. While he was fighting his management was very excited for him, but now that he is done, that management team is moving on.', 68906, 0), (436027, 'Reverse every natural instinct and do the opposite of what you are inclined to do, and you will probably come very close to having a perfect golf swing.', 31985, 0), (436028, 'Gray skies are just clouds passing over.', 65798, 0), (436029, 'Tennis is a perfect combination of violent action taking place in an atmosphere of total tranquillity.', 4882, 0), (436030, 'I want to rip out his heart and feed it to Lennox Lewis. I want to kill people. I want to rip their stomachs out and eat their children.', 11133, 0), (436031, 'Good ideas are like Nike sports shoes. They may facilitate success for an athlete who possesses them, but on their own they are nothing but an overpriced pair of sneakers. Sports shoes don''t win races. Athletes do.', 67811, 0), (436032, 'Being nerdy just means being passionate about something, including everyone - the coolest people on Earth are passionate and therefore nerdy about something whatever it is, whether it''s sports, or gaming, or technology, or fashion, or beauty, or food, or whatever.', 69290, 0), (436033, 'I never really paid attention to sports, which, coming from the mecca of football in Texas, is kind of odd. I played sports, but I was nerdy. Having a single mother, the pressure was on me to get good grades and a scholarship and go to college.', 69649, 0), (436034, 'I live by ''Go big or go home.'' That''s with everything. It''s like either commit and go for it or don''t do it at all. I apply that to everything. I apply that to relationships, I apply that to like sports, I apply that to everything. That''s what I live by. That''s how I like it.', 55738, 0), (436035, 'I think exercise tests us in so many ways, our skills, our hearts, our ability to bounce back after setbacks. This is the inner beauty of sports and competition, and it can serve us all well as adult athletes.', 65496, 0), (436036, 'I''m one of these people that likes adrenaline and new things, like extreme sports. It makes me feel alive.', 47135, 0), (436037, 'Sailing a boat calls for quick action, a blending of feeling with the wind and water as well as with the very heart and soul of the boat itself. Sailing teaches alertness and courage, and gives in return a joyousness and peace that but few sports afford.', 62529, 0), (436038, 'I won''t predict anything historic. But nothing is impossible.', 30837, 0), (436039, 'You''ll be dedicated and that''s what you should want to be in anything in life - whether it''s sports or academics or your relationship. It all stems from finding that fun, that thrill, that excitement.', 69650, 0), (436040, 'I learned early in sports that to be effective - for a player to play the best he can play - is a matter of concentration and being unaware of distractions, positive or negative.', 14943, 0), (436041, 'Pro wrestling is not fake; it''s sports entertainment. We go out there and we perform, and a lot of what we do out there is real, but we''re not going to insult anyone''s intelligence - there is a predetermined winner. It''s just the fans don''t know who it is, and that''s what makes it so intriguing.', 69651, 0), (436042, 'If it doesn''t matter who wins or loses, then why do they keep score?', 5571, 0), (436043, 'Sports play a very important role in consolidating the national strength, adding lustre to the country''s prestige and honour, inspiring people with national dignity and pride, and imbuing the whole society with revolutionary mettle.', 67852, 0), (436044, 'I''ve never met anybody who says they don''t like the World Cup. If you''re a soccer fan or not, everybody loves watching it, and I think it could be the same for other sports.', 69373, 0), (436045, 'Sports should not become routine. It should be about passion.', 69652, 0), (436046, 'If you watch a game, it''s fun. If you play it, it''s recreation. If you work at it, it''s golf.', 13132, 0), (436047, 'I wish I had played team sports. I think every kid should. Teamwork builds character - teaches people about leadership and cooperation.', 54876, 0), (436048, 'But sports carried me away from being in a gang, or being associated with drugs. Sports was my way out.', 11158, 0), (436049, 'Life wasn''t easy growing up; it was frustrating. If I had been a better reader, then that would have come easily, sports would have come easily, everything would have come easily, and I never would have realized that the way you get ahead in life is hard work.', 67828, 0), (436050, 'Life is about timing.', 38471, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436051, 'In sports, you simply aren''t considered a real champion until you have defended your title successfully. Winning it once can be a fluke; winning it twice proves you are the best.', 62515, 0), (436052, 'Don''t force your kids into sports. I never was. To this day, my dad has never asked me to go play golf. I ask him. It''s the child''s desire to play that matters, not the parent''s desire to have the child play. Fun. Keep it fun.', 11163, 0), (436053, 'I love eating it - grilled chicken, pasta, rice, and other foods that give me long term energy. Every once in a while, my sweet tooth gets the best of me and I have to snack on some candy. Beverage wise, I stick to sports drinks, water, milk, and juice.', 69653, 0), (436054, 'I think that from the time you start playing sports as a child you see that your responsibility to your team is to play the best that you can play as an individual... and yet, not take anything away from being part of a team.', 10384, 0), (436055, 'The game of golf would lose a great deal if croquet mallets and billiard cues were allowed on the putting green.', 110, 0), (436056, 'Video games offer violent messages, and even the sports video games include taunting and teasing.', 68871, 0), (436057, 'For many sports fans, the onset of fall only means one thing: It''s football season!', 32425, 0), (436058, 'When launching a product called an Energy Drink and named Red Bull, a product that stimulates body and mind, it is a short step to the roots where Red Bull came from. We have been doing this for 20 years - now it''s called adventure sports, extreme sports, and outdoor sports.', 69654, 0), (436059, 'All of my free time is made up of motor sports endeavors, be them motorcycles or off-road racing or track days. I just love anything with an engine. That is one of my main loves. Obviously, my other well-known love is Kristen Bell.', 69655, 0), (436060, 'You always get a special kick on opening day, no matter how many you go through. You look forward to it like a birthday party when you''re a kid. You think something wonderful is going to happen.', 59511, 0), (436061, 'Contrary to the royal and uptight image of polo, I want to bring it to a younger generation. This is a great sport that can have a larger audience and appeal to more people. Sportsmanship is lacking in many other sports that I don''t want to name.', 68932, 0), (436062, 'Apart from education, you need good health, and for that, you need to play sports.', 69652, 0), (436063, 'I''m a football fan, a sports fan, a fan of competition.', 2387, 0), (436064, 'These are my new shoes. They''re good shoes. They won''t make you rich like me, they won''t make you rebound like me, they definitely won''t make you handsome like me. They''ll only make you have shoes like me. That''s it.', 15009, 0), (436065, 'Sports are a microcosm of society.', 4882, 0), (436066, 'The team has come along slow but fast.', 63919, 0), (436067, 'We are raising today''s children in sterile, risk-averse and highly structured environments. In so doing, we are failing to cultivate artists, pioneers and entrepreneurs, and instead cultivating a generation of children who can follow the rules in organized sports games, sit for hours in front of screens and mark bubbles on standardized tests.', 67579, 0), (436068, 'I want to explore the world properly, to be able to write about and take pictures of all kinds of different cultures. Just be an explorer or adventurer. I also love extreme sports.', 68038, 0), (436069, 'There are two things that come very easily to me: rooting for New York sports teams and making mistakes.', 68012, 0), (436070, 'Some people are born on third base and go through life thinking they hit a triple.', 69656, 0), (436071, 'Wrestling is ballet with violence.', 16709, 0), (436072, 'You spend a good piece of your life gripping a baseball and in the end it turns out that it was the other way around all the time.', 18637, 0), (436073, 'Bulls do not win bull fights. People do.', 66748, 0), (436074, 'Golf is a game in which you yell ''fore,'' shoot six, and write down five.', 30665, 0), (436075, 'I don''t want to play golf. When I hit a ball, I want someone else to go chase it.', 69645, 0), (436076, 'I guess there is nothing that will get your mind off everything like golf. I have never been depressed enough to take up the game, but they say you get so sore at yourself you forget to hate your enemies.', 1122, 0), (436077, 'People love video games because they do things they obviously can''t do in real life. That''s especially true with sports games because fans love to step into the shoes of their favorite athletes.', 69657, 0), (436078, 'Regardless of the obstacles or hurdles that are ahead of you, regardless of the opponent, regardless of the odds, your goal and objective always is to win. I think that''s part of sports.', 69658, 0), (436079, 'I grew up on the East Coast, and we always used to say, ''Go get your hustle on,'' whether it was playing sports or making money. You do what you have to do to do what you want to do.', 69659, 0), (436080, 'I''m a visual thinker, really bad at algebra. There''s others that are a pattern thinker. These are the music and math minds. They think in patterns instead of pictures. Then there''s another type that''s not a visual thinker at all, and they''re the ones that memorize all of the sports statistics, all of the weather statistics.', 11095, 0), (436081, 'One afternoon when I was 9, my dad told me I''d be skipping school the next day. Then we drove 12 hours from Melbourne to Sydney for the Centenary Test, a once-in-a-lifetime commemorative cricket match. It was great fun - especially for a kid who was a massive sports fan.', 43985, 0), (436082, 'Bowling is all physics and energy distribution. It''s F = ma. So it is actually one of the most science-y sports, because it literally is just a ball and a surface and objects to knock down.', 11187, 0), (436083, 'Trip Hawkins - and this was the early 1980s - was saying there''s going to be a day when everyone has a computer and they''re going to want to do more on it, including playing games. So he started up a company, EA Sports, and he was going to have three games, football, basketball and baseball. So I was the football game.', 13024, 0), (436084, 'It''s a crazy world, so sports and athletics and music can be a form of escapism.', 18483, 0), (436085, 'I''ve gotten to know a lot of great people here in all the different sports. It''s fun. It''s fun to get involved where you live. And this is where I live. I''m a registered voter here. I have my Wisconsin driver''s license.', 68228, 0), (436086, 'I''m 19 now, and I go to The New School in New York, where I study Criminal Psychology. My first week of second semester was during Fashion Week when my first editorials in ''CR Fashion Book'' and ''Sports Illustrated'' came out. It was crazy!', 60670, 0), (436087, 'The ban on sports betting does exactly what Prohibition did. It makes criminals rich.', 11156, 0), (436088, 'I''m a girl, but that doesn''t mean I don''t appreciate greatness and the struggle of sports. My situation - and I''ve always said this, even in politics - is may the best man win. I''m not team-bound.', 67021, 0), (436089, 'If I wasn''t dyslexic, I probably wouldn''t have won the Games. If I had been a better reader, then that would have come easily, sports would have come easily... and I never would have realized that the way you get ahead in life is hard work.', 67828, 0), (436090, 'If you look at things that really affect people''s lives - sport, the arts, charities - they were always at the back of the queue for government money - health, social security, defence, pensions were all way ahead. And each of those areas - sports, the arts, the lottery - got relatively petty cash from the government.', 67731, 0), (436091, 'How does one control weight? By not overeating. How does one stay in shape? One plays sports. There are no magic pills here.', 50689, 0), (436092, 'Since childhood, sports has been one of the most important influences in my life.', 68105, 0), (436093, 'I''m a pretty agile guy, especially being taller and having done martial arts from about the age of 13, but parkour is one of those sports that I wish I''d discovered sooner. When my nephew first showed me, I thought, ''Damn - I''m too old for this.''', 55738, 0), (436094, 'Though teenagers are generally very interested in sports, they must realise that education is the most important thing in their lives. They must find the right balance.', 69652, 0), (436095, 'The great Comrades Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, putting forward the development of sports as a matter that has an important bearing on the prosperity of the country and nation, indicated the road ahead of the Juche-based sports and wrote a new chapter in the history of building a sports power by dint of outstanding ideas and leadership.', 67852, 0), (436096, 'I''m a big sports fan. Football. Cricket.', 67451, 0), (436097, 'Pro football is like nuclear warfare. There are no winners, only survivors.', 65798, 0), (436098, 'Trying to sneak a fastball past Hank Aaron is like trying to sneak the sunrise past a rooster.', 69660, 0), (436099, 'I used to play sports. Then I realized you can buy trophies. Now I am good at everything.', 2315, 0), (436100, 'Sports is like rock ''n'' roll. Both are dominant cultural forces, both speak an international language, and both are all about emotions.', 11344, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436101, 'Honestly, I don''t listen to nobody else''s music but my own. It''s kind of like sports to me. You don''t see Kobe Bryant at a LeBron James game - he just works on his own game. And that''s what I do. I only listen to me, so I can criticize and analyze and all those things.', 2080, 0), (436102, 'If you''re a sports fan you realize that when you meet somebody, like a girlfriend, they kind of have to root for your team. They don''t have a choice.', 61859, 0), (436103, 'In the seventies we had to make it acceptable for people to accept girls and women as athletes. We had to make it okay for them to be active. Those were much scarier times for females in sports.', 4882, 0), (436104, 'I grew up with six brothers, and I''m from Chicago, so princesses and Barbie dolls were not around the house. It was more like sports and comic books, so getting to work for Marvel is like my version of being able to be a princess.', 69661, 0), (436105, 'Sports, entertainment and aviation are three of the most exciting professions in the world; you are dealing with the same magnitude.', 69662, 0), (436106, 'If I was invincible, maybe I would take up some extreme sports.', 69663, 0), (436107, 'Relax? How can anybody relax and play golf? You have to grip the club, don''t you?', 31985, 0), (436108, 'The only time my prayers are never answered is on the golf course.', 4008, 0), (436109, 'You win some, lose some, and wreck some.', 69664, 0), (436110, 'Baseball is a game where a curve is an optical illusion, a screwball can be a pitch or a person, stealing is legal and you can spit anywhere you like except in the umpire''s eye or on the ball.', 69665, 0), (436111, 'As athletes, we''re used to reacting quickly. Here, it''s ''come, stop, come, stop.'' There''s a lot of downtime. That''s the toughest part of the day.', 1813, 0), (436112, 'I''m tired of hearing about money, money, money, money, money. I just want to play the game, drink Pepsi, wear Reebok.', 66772, 0), (436113, 'Play is the only way the highest intelligence of humankind can unfold.', 25659, 0), (436114, 'You don''t suffer, kill yourself and take the risks I take just for money. I love bike racing.', 69666, 0), (436115, 'Any time Detroit scores more than 100 points and holds the other team below 100 points they almost always win.', 59472, 0), (436116, 'Football is a simple game. Twenty-two men chase a ball for 90 minutes and at the end, the Germans always win.', 69667, 0), (436117, 'You know how sports teach kids teamwork and how to be strong and brave and confident? Improv was my sport. I learned how to not waffle and how to hold a conversation, how to take risks and actually be excited to fail.', 13298, 0), (436118, 'I have long recognized a link between fitness and mental health and I think we need to encourage young people to take part in sports and team activities because we know it has such positive results.', 67943, 0), (436119, 'Sports have always been a really important part of how I energize myself, as well as how I relax. I spend a lot of my spare time with my family playing tennis, biking and rollerblading.', 69480, 0), (436120, 'I used to practice at the hockey ground on synthetic surface while I was in the sports hostel, so Test cricket is certainly going to be a challenge for me.', 67900, 0), (436121, 'Every child should have time for arts, music, sports, drama, robotics, school newspapers and the like, not to mention recess and play.', 67231, 0), (436122, 'We wanted Nike to be the world''s best sports and fitness company. Once you say that, you have a focus. You don''t end up making wing tips or sponsoring the next Rolling Stones world tour.', 11344, 0), (436123, 'I love extreme sports, I like snowboarding and motorcross and rollerblading and hockey.', 69392, 0), (436124, 'Tiger Woods is the only sports star who''s worth every penny he makes.', 13187, 0), (436125, 'It''s kind of ironic that the two sports with the greatest characters, boxing and horse racing, have both been on the decline. In both cases it''s for the lack of a suitable hero.', 69668, 0), (436126, 'The Games are just a nice, positive way to build friendships, camaraderie and, of course, self-esteem. Plus, the Games are a great opportunity for people to participate in sports who normally wouldn''t.', 69669, 0), (436127, 'The word ''geek'' today does not mean what it used to mean. A geek isn''t the skinny kid with a pocket protector and acne. There can be computer geeks, video game geeks, car geeks, military geeks, and sports geeks. Being a geek just means that you''re passionate about something.', 68545, 0), (436128, 'The most important thing you learn as a sports photographer is anticipation - not where the action is taking place, but where it''s going to take place. Not where the subject is now, but where they''re going to be.', 69670, 0), (436129, 'Meeting sports athletes that are the best in the world is a thrill to this day.', 11344, 0), (436130, 'I like sports, and swimming is my favorite. Doing physical exercises keeps one fit and healthy and helps one work more efficiently. I think we all need to strike a balance between work and relaxation. This can keep us energetic and help us do our job better.', 67393, 0), (436131, 'In the United States, we spend millions of dollars on sports because it promotes teamwork, discipline, and the experience of learning to make great progress in small increments. Learning to play music does all this and more.', 56394, 0), (436132, 'As a father, I believe that involving children in sports at a young age is generally, a wise proposition. I believe that healthy competition is... well... healthy; that sporting events foster a spirit of teamwork that far surpasses the events themselves; and that active participation keeps children moving and is good for their self-esteem.', 66796, 0), (436133, 'Bin Laden wasn''t all that central to the terrorist network any more, but taking him down created a kind of national catharsis. It''s been a really, really long time since we had something to celebrate that didn''t involve a sports team. I''d rather it had been a non-death-related occasion, but we''ll take what we can get.', 19519, 0), (436134, 'I''m a golfer, and what are the two sports you can do till you drop? Golf and surfing. They''re great for you limber-wise, they''re great for you health-wise, and they put you in sweet locations.', 2387, 0), (436135, 'When I get into a bad mood, I do sports and then everything''s OK. And then I go and make decisions, however painful they may be.', 69671, 0), (436136, 'Psychology is much bigger than just medicine, or fixing unhealthy things. It''s about education, work, marriage - it''s even about sports. What I want to do is see psychologists working to help people build strengths in all these domains.', 67434, 0), (436137, 'Nobody wants to buy a $60,000 electric Civic. But people will pay $90,000 for an electric sports car.', 10864, 0), (436138, 'I like sports. I''m a big football fan. When I was a kid, I was a... I don''t even know how to describe it... I was an obsessed Brooklyn Dodgers fan. And I think when they left Brooklyn, which was simultaneous with me starting college, everything changed, and I haven''t had the same passion for sports.', 66875, 0), (436139, 'I was all-state in four sports in New Jersey, but sometimes I couldn''t get served at a restaurant two blocks from my high school. There were no job opportunities then... the only thing a black youth could aspire to be was a bellboy or a pullman or an elevator operator, or, maybe, a teacher. There was a time when all we had was black baseball.', 69672, 0), (436140, 'I think my appeal is that I''ve always tried to stay very grounded to my fans and to be accessible - not being this unattainable thing. I think doing sports and riding motorcycles has made me more approachable and more real and down to earth.', 69673, 0), (436141, 'Bringing more large sporting events to Africa would help the continent develop sports policies and at the same time optimize its peoples'' chances of achieving competitive success.', 67494, 0), (436142, 'Science has taught us, against all intuition, that apparently solid things like crystals and rocks are really almost entirely composed of empty space. And the familiar illustration is the nucleus of an atom is a fly in the middle of a sports stadium, and the next atom is in the next sports stadium.', 1716, 0), (436143, 'I am just enjoying what cricket has given me. In sports, it''s obviously really important for all of us to remain fit - and health is wealth, so health comes with the sport.', 69674, 0), (436144, 'Lake Pend Oreille is definitely my favorite place to be while in Sandpoint. I love to get out on a boat to enjoy water sports, camping, fishing, or just to relax and catch a sunset.', 69675, 0), (436145, 'In sports, every day you can be the hero or the goat.', 69676, 0), (436146, 'For watching sports, I tend to drink Guinness; early evenings always begin well with a Grey Goose and tonic with plenty of lime; and on a cold winter''s night, there''s nothing quite like a glass of Black Maple Hill... an absolute peach of a bourbon.', 66766, 0), (436147, 'Like great teams in sports and business endeavors, if there''s a chemistry among the participants, and they truly enjoy fellowship together, everybody wants to be there, stay involved, and just have fun together.', 69677, 0), (436148, 'Sports gives us the grandest opportunity of all to talk about reaching down and helping up or getting on somebody else''s shoulders.', 69678, 0), (436149, 'I paid more for the Dallas Cowboys than anyone prior than that had ever paid to get involved in sports. But I wanted to be a part of the future of the Dallas Cowboys.', 69678, 0), (436150, 'Equality for men and women, across the world, not only in sports, is the goal. We obviously have a long way to go, but every little bit helps.', 37889, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436151, 'Sports are a great place to show that equality can happen.', 37889, 0), (436152, 'I know that some of the finest writing I''ve ever read has been sports writing, whatever the topic was, whatever the sport they were writing about. It seems to be an area where people are allowed a little more leeway than when they''re reporting on traffic jams and city-council meetings.', 3175, 0), (436153, 'Sports uplift us. It''s celebratory, gives us optimism and joy.', 69679, 0), (436154, 'I think it''s huge, especially in team sports, for players to be able to rely on each other and to really trust in each other.', 67841, 0), (436155, 'I''ve told Billy if I ever caught him cheating, I wouldn''t kill him because I love his children and they need a dad. But I would beat him up. I know where all of his sports injuries are.', 1380, 0), (436156, 'We''re not doing outrageous fashion; I make sports clothes that are relatively conservative, clothes that everyone wears.', 66804, 0), (436157, 'I wasn''t really a work-conscious type of person. I was a player. I loved to play sports.', 1813, 0), (436158, 'There are kids who get on a BMX bike when they''re eight years old and they go, ''Whoa, this is incredible,'' and grow up to do extreme sports. It''s the same for me with acting.', 68461, 0), (436159, 'I think the Cowboys are one of only two teams in all of sports that engender love and hate to that extreme. The other is the Yankees. You love the Yankees or you hate the Yankees.', 69680, 0), (436160, 'I''m excited to join my brother-in-law Ken Thomson every Tuesday night on SiriusXM to recap all of the awesome NFL action, and to find out what in the Wylde world of sports is going on.', 69681, 0), (436161, 'Eventually you won''t think of ''the Internet business.'' You''ll think of it more like news, weather, sports, but even that taxonomy isn''t clear.', 1133, 0), (436162, 'Some of the companies we helped start are names you know. An office supply company called Staples - where I''m pleased to see the Obama campaign has been shopping; The Sports Authority, which became a favorite of my sons. We started an early childhood learning center called Bright Horizons that First Lady Michelle Obama rightly praised.', 52321, 0), (436163, 'I hate all sports as rabidly as a person who likes sports hates common sense.', 411, 0), (436164, 'I used to play a lot of racket sports, tennis and squash.', 68421, 0), (436165, 'I come from a family that has always emphasized and enjoyed sports - golf, tennis, football, baseball and the rest.', 60667, 0), (436166, 'I don''t know anything that builds the will to win better than competitive sports.', 9695, 0), (436167, 'You cannot mix sports with politics.', 67756, 0), (436168, 'I was brought up to believe that it''s family first. Of all the people my parents knew, the family was most important. You always turn to your family, and the family supports you. We do what we can to support our young and go and see the grandchildren if they''re doing plays at school and their sports events.', 43810, 0), (436169, 'Some people go off to an ashram or they, you know, have a midlife crisis and buy a sports car. For me, I do ''Hedwig,'' and I see it''s a midlife crisis maybe, and I see what''s next. And it''s a good trampoline, maybe, into the next part of my life.', 57404, 0), (436170, 'All the minor sports injuries you acquire over the years begin to multiply like flies when you get over 70.', 18244, 0), (436171, 'Great performers - in sports, the arts, business, or whatever field - have undertaken massive amounts of training. And when that training is complete... they train some more, and harder than they expect to perform. Why? Training builds confidence and ensures peak performance.', 68864, 0), (436172, 'I''m not into extreme sports or something. I just live a quiet life.', 1570, 0), (436173, 'I''ve been playing sports since I was five. For me, there''s no happier moment than when I''m out in the woods on a bike or a run. I feel on top of the world, and nothing else makes me feel that way.', 69682, 0), (436174, 'Discrimination and prejudice of any kind have no place in sports or in our society.', 69683, 0), (436175, 'Golf is a day spent in a round of strenuous idleness.', 2063, 0), (436176, 'In sports and in business, the greatest leaders are those who make the best decisions in the most crucial of situations. They are the ones who focus their energy on turning tough decisions into winning decisions.', 69684, 0), (436177, 'Hitting is timing. Pitching is upsetting timing.', 65752, 0), (436178, 'Everyone thought I was going to die like a year later, they didn''t know. So I helped educate sports, and then the world, that a man living with HIV can play basketball. He''s not going to give it to anybody by playing basketball.', 67024, 0), (436179, 'I was socially isolated as a kid. I had friends, but I wasn''t very good at sports and that sort of thing so I became quite comfortable being by myself, exploring. The world was my private playground, and in it, I was supreme. Darwin, Faraday, Huxley and other great scientists were my companions.', 68660, 0), (436180, 'I have never cared especially for outdoor sports and have no desire to excel at tennis, swimming, or golf. I''ll leave those things to the men.', 1, 0), (436181, 'I did everything when I started. In Miami I did news, I did weather, I did sports, I did disk-jockeying. And I did a sports talk show every week - every Saturday night.', 10298, 0), (436182, 'My favorite was always whichever sport was in season. I think these days it''s almost saddening to see kids who are 10 or 11 and are forced to choose one sport and specialize in that sport and play that sport year-round. By playing different sports... you become a better all-around athlete.', 69685, 0), (436183, 'I know when I have kids, when I''m older, I''m going to encourage them to play sports because I think it teaches you a lot. It teaches you discipline, teamwork, and that there''s really no ''I'' in team.', 69686, 0), (436184, 'I believe God created sports for a good reason. It''s recreation. It''s something that we enjoy. It teaches us a lot as well... I believe God is a sports fan.', 67206, 0), (436185, 'In Boston, they love their sports celebrities. And it''s great.', 66949, 0), (436186, 'Every boy learns more in his hours of play than in his hours of labor. In school, he lays in the materials of thinking, but in his sports, he actually thinks: he whets his faculties, and he opens his eyes.', 20151, 0), (436187, 'You know it''s going to hell when the best rapper out there is white and the best golfer is black.', 15009, 0), (436188, 'If you think it''s hard to meet new people, try picking up the wrong golf ball.', 14563, 0), (436189, 'Growing up in Huntington Beach, you were either a traditional sports athlete, a skateboarder, or a surfer. I got my first skateboard when I was five and skated off and on over the years, did a little BMX racing as a kid, and then in my freshman or sophomore year I started getting a little bit more into skateboarding.', 69687, 0), (436190, 'I grew up thinking that I would become a fighter pilot and was fascinated by aircrafts as I had grown up around that. But my father encouraged me to not become an Air Force person, given the varied interests I had, be it books, movies, sports or fighter flying.', 69688, 0), (436191, 'A geek isn''t the skinny kid with a pocket protector and acne. There can be computer geeks, video game geeks, car geeks, military geeks, and sports geeks. Being a geek just means that you''re passionate about something.', 68545, 0), (436192, 'Ethnic prejudice has no place in sports, and baseball must recognize that truth if it is to maintain stature as a national game.', 62664, 0), (436193, 'I think sports are extremely beneficial for our youth. They parallel life in so many ways.', 64904, 0), (436194, 'The best thing about the Kentucky Derby is that it is only two minutes long. It is the quickest event in sports, except for Sumo-wrestling & Mike Tyson fights. Maybe Drag-racing is quicker, but I have never been attracted to it.', 126, 0), (436195, 'Sport is a wonderful metaphor for life. Of all the sports that I played - skiing, baseball, fishing - there is no greater example than golf, because you''re playing against yourself and nature.', 20594, 0), (436196, 'Sports is the only entertainment where, no matter how many times you go back, you never know the ending.', 29433, 0), (436197, 'Baseball is almost the only orderly thing in a very unorderly world. If you get three strikes, even the best lawyer in the world can''t get you off.', 59461, 0), (436198, 'If a lot of people gripped a knife and fork the way they do a golf club, they''d starve to death.', 44942, 0), (436199, 'I love outdoor sports, like volleyball, and I play them whenever I can.', 47135, 0), (436200, 'We live in a world where sports have the potential to bridge the gap between racism, sexism and discrimination. The 2012 Olympic Games was a great start but hopefully what these games taught us is that if women are given an opportunity on an equal playing field the possibilities for women are endless.', 63993, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436201, 'Jamaica is more than just the ''brand'' the world recognizes so well; it''s a place of pride for the people who live here, its educational institutions, its sports achievements, its science and technology growth.', 69689, 0), (436202, 'Many high school students are under so much competitive pressure. They are sometimes taught that if they don''t have a 4.0 GPA, score in the 99th percentile on admissions tests, and demonstrate leadership in sports and participate in clubs, they won''t get into college anywhere. Even highly credentialed professionals get caught up in this.', 69690, 0), (436203, 'The tradition in Serbia has always been team sports - football, basketball, handball, volleyball and water polo, individual sports are not supported.', 69515, 0), (436204, 'All good sports reporters know that the best stories are in the loser''s locker room.', 2553, 0), (436205, 'The uglier a man''s legs are, the better he plays golf - it''s almost a law.', 3173, 0), (436206, 'I''ll let the racket do the talking.', 63558, 0), (436207, 'I''d just as soon play tennis with the net down.', 35, 0), (436208, 'I think extreme sports are really good for relieving stress.', 13006, 0), (436209, 'In a world as competitive as ours, the child who does not get a decent education is condemned to the fringes of society. I think all Australians agree that this is intolerable. So we must demand as much of our schools as we do of our sports teams - and ensure that they keep the Australian dream alive for every child.', 15116, 0), (436210, 'Sports is the toy department of human life.', 69691, 0), (436211, 'Where there is peace, there is sports; where there is sports, there is peace. Peace is what allows us, especially young people, to dream, go after one''s goals and prepare you for the next challenge in life.', 67489, 0), (436212, 'Boxing is a celebration of the lost religion of masculinity all the more trenchant for its being lost.', 852, 0), (436213, 'Golf is a game in which one endeavors to control a ball with implements ill adapted for the purpose.', 1970, 0), (436214, 'Baseball life is a tough life on the family.', 69692, 0), (436215, 'You''ve got to enjoy time with your family and friends, and if you''re involved in sports franchises, those peak moments in playoff games. You have to enjoy life.', 34870, 0), (436216, 'I just got hooked on the radio, the voice of it all. It was my connection to metropolitan America, if you will. Sports, in particularly baseball then ''cause of its rich sediment of numbers, was one of the first things a young person could peg up with adults on - that is, you could know as much about Jimmy Fox as your father did.', 29034, 0), (436217, 'Black people dominate sports in the United States. 20% of the population and 90% of the final four.', 2171, 0), (436218, 'Talk radio has almost ruined the sports fan.', 69693, 0), (436219, 'Sports betting is all about money management, so the most money won on one event is not the most important thing.', 69694, 0), (436220, 'As a result of Title IX, and a new generation of parents who want their daughters to have the opportunities they never had, women''s sports have arrived.', 69695, 0), (436221, 'The things that people do now in sports, you can''t even believe. These are complete total athletes. To see what human beings can do in the highest level is amazing.', 52296, 0), (436222, 'There''s a whole lot more to the African-American community than entertainment and sports.', 67449, 0), (436223, 'I learned early on, stay away from politics, stay away from religion and don''t talk about sports. Those three right there will get you in trouble.', 69696, 0), (436224, 'Growing up, I looked up to major league baseball players, and now these young women have amazing, incredible women all across the board, from swimming to gymnastics to softball to basketball. It is incredible how far women have come and women in sports have come.', 69697, 0), (436225, 'When we talk about reviews, what we are really talking about is just a market report - it''s like reading about the new Lexus. You have to know what the guy writing the review cares about to understand his take. Does he like sports cars, or does he like Bentleys?', 23139, 0), (436226, 'I still feel that in India we look upon sports as a recreational activity - which it is - but people have to understand that there is a career in sports. It''s not just necessary to be a doctor or a lawyer or an engineer, as most of us Indians appear to think that our children should grow up to be.', 67107, 0), (436227, 'When I was little, I guess I was just an ordinary kid. But then things changed when I was in junior high. You know, kids that become geeks become one because of something. Like, they aren''t good at sports, or girls don''t like them. I, too, for some reason, got into things like science fiction and, well, especially science fiction as an escape.', 69698, 0), (436228, 'Leadership is one of sports'' intangibles. Guys can score, guys can fight, guys can skate faster than anybody else. But not everybody can say, ''Follow me.''', 56478, 0), (436229, 'I grew up in a very ''Friday Night Lights,'' sports-focused town. I did not play the sports. I was never bullied physically, but I was called names. I was also an overweight kid. I knew what it''s like to feel like the other, to feel written off for things that were not in my control - my appearance, my interests.', 69699, 0), (436230, 'The political hero is not like the sports champion or matinee idol or daring inventor; like the war hero, he is born only of tragedy.', 13613, 0), (436231, 'To be honest, I''m shocked the University of Washington''s sports teams are called the Huskies. Why haven''t the Leftists that run this entire state demanded they be renamed the ''Athletes of Size'' so as to not fat shame anyone?', 8420, 0), (436232, 'The diet for climbing all the time isn''t really different from the diet for living. It''s not like cardio sports where you''re burning a bajillion calories every day.', 69700, 0), (436233, 'Thus so wretched is man that he would weary even without any cause for weariness... and so frivolous is he that, though full of a thousand reasons for weariness, the least thing, such as playing billiards or hitting a ball, is sufficient enough to amuse him.', 144, 0), (436234, 'A lifetime of training for just ten seconds.', 16509, 0), (436235, 'Football is violence and cold weather and sex and college rye.', 46208, 0), (436236, 'I grew up in New York City, where we played highly unorganized sports: stick ball, stoop ball, and the occasional game of baseball with no adult supervision.', 19511, 0), (436237, 'It''s hard to create new friendships outside sports.', 4052, 0), (436238, 'It is hard to compete with other sports. Badminton is a sport which, when compared with football and tennis, still needs promotion.', 69701, 0), (436239, 'After one Olympics, if we invest in sports and say we will get a gold medal in the next Olympic, it doesn''t work like that in sports. How it works is that you provide the infrastructure, provide education about nutrition and health.', 69702, 0), (436240, 'There''s food and supplements that you can take legally that will better your body and help you stay healthy. Shortcuts are something that''s always been around all sports, but as a union, we''re trying to do the best we can to weed those guys out of the game.', 69703, 0), (436241, 'What other people may find in poetry or art museums, I find in the flight of a good drive.', 24450, 0), (436242, 'The only thing a golfer needs is more daylight.', 31985, 0), (436243, 'If I weren''t earning $3 million a year to dunk a basketball, most people on the street would run in the other direction if they saw me coming.', 15009, 0), (436244, 'If you drink don''t drive. Don''t even putt.', 60322, 0), (436245, 'The only way to prove that you''re a good sport is to lose.', 66774, 0), (436246, 'He''s got an overall flair for the game. It looks to me like he really loves what he does and he can''t wait to get up in the morning, go hit some balls and go play.', 69704, 0), (436247, 'I had pro offers from the Detroit Lions and Green Bay Packers, who were pretty hard up for linemen in those days. If I had gone into professional football the name Jerry Ford might have been a household word today.', 10283, 0), (436248, 'I regard golf as an expensive way of playing marbles.', 67663, 0), (436249, 'Eighteen holes of match play will teach you more about your foe than 18 years of dealing with him across a desk.', 11281, 0), (436250, 'The triple is the most exciting play in baseball. Home runs win a lot of games, but I never understood why fans are so obsessed with them.', 59444, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436251, 'Baseball players are smarter than football players. How often do you see a baseball team penalized for too many men on the field?', 18637, 0), (436252, 'Golf appeals to the idiot in us and the child. Just how childlike golf players become is proven by their frequent inability to count past five.', 135, 0), (436253, 'He hits it long. His shoulders are impressively quick through the ball. That''s where he''s getting his power from. He''s young and has great elasticity.', 69705, 0), (436254, 'Fans don''t boo nobodies.', 65245, 0), (436255, 'The difference between the old ballplayer and the new ballplayer is the jersey. The old ballplayer cared about the name on the front. The new ballplayer cares about the name on the back.', 68062, 0), (436256, 'Nobody roots for Goliath.', 59443, 0), (436257, 'If a tie is like kissing your sister, losing is like kissing you grandmother with her teeth out.', 13197, 0), (436258, 'Many baseball fans look upon an umpire as a sort of necessary evil to the luxury of baseball, like the odor that follows an automobile.', 62390, 0), (436259, 'All sports for all people.', 59474, 0), (436260, 'I''m a competitive person and I love the challenge of mastering new things.', 68093, 0), (436261, 'The Olympic Games must not be an end in itself, they must be a means of creating a vast programme of physical education and sports competitions for all young people.', 69706, 0), (436262, 'I enjoyed being involved in team sports and making close friendships.', 69707, 0), (436263, 'The American people are sheep. They''re comfortable, rich, working. It''s like the Romans, they''re happy with bread and their spectator sports. The Super Bowl means more to them than any right.', 7905, 0), (436264, 'The importance that our society attaches to sport is incredible. After all, is football a game or a religion? The people of this country have allowed sports to get completely out of hand.', 69691, 0), (436265, 'My priority is to turn people - especially kids - on to sports and being active so they don''t even have to think about it being good for their health. If people participate for the fun of it, and believe me - it is fun, then fitness programs will be much more successful.', 68389, 0), (436266, 'I was very fortunate to play sports. All the anger in me went out. I had to do what I had to do. If you stay angry all the time, then you really don''t have a good life.', 64941, 0), (436267, 'The addiction to sports, therefore, in a peculiar degree marks an arrested development in man''s moral nature.', 52621, 0), (436268, 'Sports without music, it''s nothing but a game. Music adds the emotion.', 26404, 0), (436269, 'Amateurism is the strongest form of discrimination in sports. Because it discriminates against the underprivileged, it discriminates against the poor. If we want sports to go back to the wealthy, let''s make it amateur again.', 38471, 0), (436270, 'I did all the right things in so many tournaments. But like I said, sometimes in sports it just goes the other way. Maybe you''ve already won so much that it evens it out a bit sometimes. I don''t know.', 67701, 0), (436271, 'I''m not good at anything except writing jokes. I wasn''t good at sports, I wasn''t good at anything artsy, ever. I think there was a real worry for a while about what I would be good at. I was just this chubby little Indian kid who looked like a nerd.', 1289, 0), (436272, 'That''s the biggest gap in sports, the difference between the winner and the loser of the Super Bowl.', 13024, 0), (436273, 'Sports and entertainment are the only places where inner-city kids see themselves being able to succeed. Their intellectual development is something they don''t relate to.', 19298, 0), (436274, 'I''ve always been really active. I grew up playing sports, so I''m always shooting hoops or throwing the football with my friends. I''m super-active in that sense.', 69198, 0), (436275, 'I was focused on athletics, outdoors, sports.', 11154, 0), (436276, 'I also have a soft spot for spicy chicken wings. They are always best eaten at dives and sports bars, like Wogie''s in the West Village, New York City, near my house.', 69708, 0), (436277, 'I worked at my high school newspaper at Andover, which came out weekly, unusual for a high school paper. Then my first day at Penn I went right to the ''Daily Pennsylvanian'' and pretty much spent most of my college career working both as the sports editor and then editor of the editorial page.', 50715, 0), (436278, 'When a sports movie really works, it gets you on all levels, because the stakes are high. It''s black and white. It''s win or lose.', 69709, 0), (436279, 'If architecture is, as is sometimes said, music set in concrete, then football and basketball may be said to be creativity embodied in team sports.', 69710, 0), (436280, 'The BBC sports department when I was there was seriously to the right of Ghengis Khan, and if people think I am strange, they should have met some of the production staff I worked with. Margaret Thatcher and the Queen were the pin up girls for many of them.', 21153, 0), (436281, 'Sports fans have been mistreated for a long time. They have overpaid for inferior food and they have had poor service.', 69711, 0), (436282, 'You know, I never really paid attention to sports, which, coming from the mecca of football in Texas, is kind of odd. I played sports, but I was nerdy. Having a single mother, the pressure was on me to get good grades and a scholarship and go to college.', 69649, 0), (436283, 'American sports are quite masculine. And football - although it''s still played by men all over the world - football compared to American football is quite feminine in its artistry. And there''s no padding. It''s America''s loss, though.', 13014, 0), (436284, 'My love for sports will never die. I love martial arts and I want to promote it in whichever way I can. I am a fighter first, then an actor.', 67344, 0), (436285, 'Compared to politics, I think sports is funnier, because it''s inconsequential. And politics can be real important and all that. The more pointless something is, the funnier it is, you know?', 66936, 0), (436286, 'Political columnists and sports pundits are rewarded for being overconfident.', 6017, 0), (436287, 'My son has taken liking for sports and is most of the time playing cricket and football. It is so much fun being with them, as I''m enjoying every phase of motherhood.', 67813, 0), (436288, 'In 1964, when Lee Iacocca said, ''Shelby, I want you to make a sports car out of the Mustang,'' the first thing I said was, ''Lee, you can''t make a race horse out of a mule. I don''t want to do it.'' He said, ''I didn''t ask you to make it; you work for me.''', 66976, 0), (436289, 'I have always maintained that if you work hard, it won''t go waste, as recognition will come to you at some stage, whether in studies or sports. You need to have good intentions and intent to move ahead in life as well as in sports.', 67900, 0), (436290, 'You always hear that tragedies put sports in perspective, that they prove we shouldn''t care this much about the successes and failures of a bunch of wealthy strangers. I''m going the other way - sometimes, sports put everything else in perspective.', 69712, 0), (436291, 'When I was a little kid growing up in Iceland, I always dreamed about creating something that could have an impact on the whole world, and even as a young boy I was passionate about fitness and sports.', 69253, 0), (436292, 'Compared to politics, I think sports is funnier, because it''s inconsequential. And politics can be real important and all that. The more pointless something is, the funnier it is, you know? And the more grave or important things are... You know, some comedians can get this disease where they get serious all the time.', 66936, 0), (436293, 'I''ve always liked speed. I own a car that I shouldn''t be talking about because I''m an environmentalist, but the 1955 Porsche Spyder 550 RS is the finest sports car ever made.', 20594, 0), (436294, 'I have learned, in my life and work as a sportswriter, that big-time Sports and big-time Politics are not so far apart in America. They are both a means to the same end, which is victory... And why not? Victory is good for you, and don''t let anybody tell you different.', 126, 0), (436295, 'Politics should not interfere with sports. And sports should impact politics.', 50689, 0), (436296, 'Everyone thinks I''m this jock of a woman, but I didn''t play any sports. I didn''t even let my kids play baseball because I was afraid they were going to get hit by balls.', 69713, 0), (436297, 'Global sports tournaments have a range of benefits that go far beyond the games themselves. They can transform the image of a country or a region. They bring people together and reveal new possibilities to a nation''s youth.', 67494, 0), (436298, '''Potato-chip news'' is news that''s repetitive, requires little effort to absorb, and is consumable in massive quantities: true crime, natural disasters, political punditry, celebrity gossip, sports gossip, or endless photographs of beautiful houses, food, or clothes.', 3243, 0), (436299, 'I won''t have any competitive instincts in any sports, other than golf. I can''t see being competitive in sports any more.', 1813, 0), (436300, 'J.J. Watt is larger than life and Houston''s newest sports hero, in every sense of the word. He is a guy who spends NFL Fridays at high school football games and actively seeks out those in need of his kindness.', 69714, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (436301, 'Drama is played at the pace of chess... or billiards... or poker. Engrossing? Sure. But comedy is played at the jubilant, high-octane speed of sports like basketball or hockey.', 60918, 0), (436302, 'Team sports are very important for shaping personalities. It''s important that kids understand the mentality behind playing team sports and playing for one another and playing with friends.', 69715, 0), (436303, 'I grew up a Michael Jordan fan; that was my first idol. But my true sports idol was Deion Sanders: he was the person I always wanted to be. I wanted to play two sports professionally, which would never happen, but to me, that was every kid''s dream.', 69716, 0), (436304, 'Our philosophy is you need to give nonprofit money for health, nutrition, education, culture, and sports.', 66736, 0), (436305, 'It''s great to listen to men talk about sports or fights or war or even hunting sometimes, but the presence of the other, the presence of art and beauty, which crude masculinity seems to discount, is essential. Real civilization and real manhood seem to me to include those.', 9834, 0), (436306, 'I always liked to write and had fun writing, but I didn''t have any pretensions about being a writer. I liked to read and liked to putz around and write little stories or poems, but my thing was sports.', 27398, 0), (436307, 'When I was younger, I used to bite my nails so bad. I used to play sports; I played, like, every sport. I would be playing soccer, and I''d be in the middle of the field just zoned out, biting my nails, and I''d, like, miss the ball going past me.', 68261, 0), (436308, 'For me to be with someone, he''s got to be fit. Or at least doing something he loves. Following your passion - whether it''s hiking or sports or whatever - is super sexy.', 68257, 0), (436309, 'My becoming a film actor was more a twist of tale than a chosen course because I dared not to think I could ever become an actor. I couldn''t even walk up on a stage and say ''Thank you'' when we were to receive trophies at our sports meets at college.', 69717, 0), (436310, 'I never use the word ''hero'' in sports. Hero is way above ''star.'' I save ''star'' for sports. Sports is entertainment that''s all it is. ', 69718, 0), (436311, 'We knew sports was important to us and our family, but there are priorities in life.Obviously, faith is foremost; how we did in school is important. If we didn''t handle that business then there were no privileges.', 69121, 0), (436312, 'Whatever free time I get, I love to catch news and sports shows.', 68907, 0), (436313, 'I get a lot of letters that say, ''I''m a normal, down-to-earth girl. I love to cook, and I love sports.'' What I also get are letters from a whole bunch of moms saying, ''My daughter is awesome,'' and, ''My daughter is a great daughter.''', 69347, 0), (436314, 'Cleveland''s a great city. I love the city. The people here are awesome. They''re loyal and hard-working, and they''re loyal to our sports scene, and things are changing here.', 69719, 0), (436315, 'Unless you enjoy life passionately, you cannot be a good artiste. Practise what you like, be it sports or dancing.', 69720, 0), (436316, 'The idea of growing up in the South and being a man is an interesting thing; there''s a lot masculinity involved, with hunting, fishing, and playing sports that rural people take pride in, but at the same time, I grew up really not wanting to hate anybody.', 69133, 0), (436317, 'I wanted to really ingrain myself in the culture and the people. And I apologize about having an allergy to dairy products that gives me some irritable bowels, but other than that, I mean, I''ve embraced just about everything else Wisconsin - especially when it comes to sports, but also the people and the interactions with our fans.', 68228, 0), (436318, 'The problem with winter sports is that - follow me closely here - they generally take place in winter.', 2223, 0), (436319, 'Sports is human life in microcosm.', 69691, 0), (436320, 'In the field of sports you are more or less accepted for what you do rather than what you are.', 62515, 0), (436321, 'I sort of try to write everything for me. I''m a huge sports fan but have no interest in minutiae. I don''t remember who won Super Bowls five years ago or listen to sports talk radio. I''m trying to make sure the jokes are self-contained so they''re accessible to everyone.', 66936, 0), (436322, 'It sounds like a cliche, but it... you do sing about what you know about. And I grew up in a small town, and I grew up in a place where your whole world revolved around friends, family, school, and church, and sports.', 22682, 0), (436323, 'Actually, I always dreamed about getting a gold medal in the 100-meter freestyle in Olympic swimming. I always thought that would be the epic award in sports to get.', 69721, 0), (436324, 'It''s not just the kid who''s spent every penny from his job to upgrade his car to tell the world he cares about sports cars, it''s also the person driving around in a fuel-conscious hybrid electric car, because it''s more a message to the world than an effective means of saving fuel, to be quite honest.', 17174, 0), (436325, 'I wasn''t into sports when I was younger. I was one of those kids who always tried to get a note from the doctor to say I had a cold so I didn''t have to go play hockey in bad weather and be miserable.', 69722, 0), (436326, 'I like a few vintage Rolexes, and Panerais are good. I''m not into sports watches - I like chronometers.', 68421, 0), (436327, 'I''m a great sports fan, you know. I love to watch tennis and basketball and baseball and so on.', 30191, 0), (436328, 'When I played sports, if you lose the game, and then you complain, that makes you a sore loser. That doesn''t make you protester - that just makes you a whiner.', 69723, 0), (436329, 'When I was a kid, I did many sports. Judo, like my dad, but also volleyball, handball, and gymnastics. We never