o have been successful need to help other sports, those sports that are just emerging. That''s what I''ve been thinking about and looking forward to.', 37889, 0), (436374, 'Tennis has been around for so long - women have been playing the majors since the 1800s. Other sports have not had professional leagues for women for as long.', 37889, 0), (436375, 'Tennis is definitely a star for women in sports.', 37889, 0), (436376, 'I spent my whole life playing sports and training and pushing myself to the limits.', 37889, 0), (436377, 'My deep dark secret is that I was a nerd in school. I liked the theater. I liked to study. I wasn''t very good at sports.', 12642, 0), (436378, 'At home I have a copy of the April 21, 1986, issue of ''Sports Illustrated.'' I''m on the cover with the blurb, ''Can Lou Do It?'' I''d just arrived at Notre Dame, and with spring football underway, I was the focal point of that week''s coverage.', 2081, 0), (436379, 'I look at athletes in all sports and try to picture what kind of football player they''d be, what position they''d play and so on.', 2081, 0), (436380, 'Pittsburgh felt like the perfect size of a city to me. There''s enough to do, but it''s not like living in a circus. I also really loved how sports-enthusiastic Pittsburgh people are: how proud of their sports they are.', 67004, 0), (436381, 'There aren''t a lot of opportunities for that rite of passage that makes you a man. War is one of them, and violent sports are another.', 35699, 0), (436382, 'I like a deep sports massage - a casual beating up. I try to get them whenever I can, usually more if I''m getting in shape for a role.', 12497, 0), (436383, 'I wasn''t good in school. I didn''t do sports. I sat in the bedroom and listened to records. Because the Beatles did whatever they wanted to, I took that as a kid and said, ''That''s what rock is.''', 49828, 0), (436384, 'I''m sort of like a lame, single guy in a red sports car.', 4019, 0), (436385, 'I''m actually a fan of all of the EA